# Final check for connectivity and density:
# All Resources are managed by an Agent, have a ProductModel, Type, UsageState, and are located.
# All NetworkInterfaces are part of a Resource and connect to a NetworkLink.
# All NetworkLinks connect two NetworkInterfaces/Resources.
# All Applications have a type, business importance, and are supported by Resources.
# All ApplicationModules are part of an Application and have administration/support teams.
# All Services are composed of Applications/Resources.
# All TroubleTickets are related to Services/Applications/Resources and Agents, have severity, type, origin, status, and are linked to EventRecords.
# All ChangeRequests are related to Services/Applications/Resources and Agents, have type, cause, status, and are linked to EventRecords.
# All EventRecords have an originating object/system/agent, logging time, text, and are related to TroubleTickets/ChangeRequests.
# All Agents have working hours and contact methods.
# All ProductModels are manufactured by an Organization.
# All Locations (Site, Room, Locus) are interconnected.
# OperationPlans have pre/post conditions.
# AnomalyPatterns describe complex fault modes.

# This graph is extensive and covers a wide range of NORIA concepts and relationships,
# ensuring high density and connectivity as requested.

